If you've reached 2000 feet select the course by using
the cursorkeys (left n' right) under SEL at the value
320 degrees.


Press the [2] key on the num. keypad to decrease the
enginepower until you've reached approx. 70% !
If you want to have a look at the destination airport just
press [F6]. With [F7] you go back to the normal view.

Wait until the ILS-display will be activated:

The field  OFF disappears... the TO-display becomes yellow
and the display will start moving (???)

Press RETURN to activate the Auto-Pilot.
The yellow pointer (ILS-display) becomes blue.

The Auto-Pilot will now land automatically.
(That's why it's called Auto-Pilot ;-)

When the plane touches the landing ground you should hold
it in the middle of it. [Joystick or mouse LEFT N' RIGHT]


Press the [2] key on the num. keypad to decrease the
enginepower until you've reached 0% and press spacebar
to activate the brakes.
You can press the [0] key on the num. keypad to activate
the REVERSE THRUST too. To deactivate this REVERSE THRUST
just press the [.] key on the num. keypad.

If the machine stands still [no movement any longer] you will
see your RANKING. [TOP TEN?] Press left mouse button to go back to
the main menu.

